com.phunware.locationmessaging.log

Interface Logger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompositeLogger, FileLogger, LogLogger, VoidLogger

    public interface Logger
    A Logger handles log messages and errors at different log levels. Implementations of this class need to be performant, as log messages can be sent on the main thread and in tight loops. If the Logger implementation needs any sort File I/O or network related calls, it should manage it's own thread and pass the calls accordingly.
